# Verify lint and build after changes

After completing non-trivial edits (especially to `src/`, config, or dependencies), run checks locally before considering the task done:

1. **`npm run lint`** — fix ESLint issues introduced or exposed by the change.
2. **`npm run build`** — ensure TypeScript and Vite production build succeed.

If a change is intentionally tiny (e.g. a one-line comment) and cannot affect compilation, skipping is reasonable; for anything that touches imports, types, or components, run both.
